-- Google sees significant capex investment continuing
-- 
-- Wed Jan 31, 2007 5:04pm EST
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2007/01/31/us-google-capex-idUSWEN328420070131

 

 NEW YORK  (Reuters) - Internet search leader Google Inc. ( GOOG.O ) said on Wednesday its expects a significant rate of capital spending to continue for the foreseeable future as it aims to capture an ever larger amount of Web advertising. 


 Google Chief Financial Officer George Reyes told investors on a conference call that the company expects significant investment in its technology infrastructure, as well as continued growth in staffing, investments in advertising partnerships and Internet services. The company paid out more than $3 billion to affiliates that carried Google ads during 2006. "This is a figure that is going to increase as we ramp up our video, radio and brand advertising," Google co-founder and president Sergey Brin told investors on a conference call following the company's fourth-quarter earnings report.